<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10216466>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Aloe khamiesensis subsp. khamiesensis. A. Known distribution (red shading). B. Tall plant with unbranched stem. C. Rosette of dull green leaves with a few white spots. D. Plant with branched stem and numerous rosettes. E. Raceme with orange-red, greenish yellow-tipped flowers. Photographs: B, C, E. Marinda Koekemoer (Concordia, Northern Cape, South Africa, July 2013); D. Arrie W. Klopper (Kamieskroon, Northern Cape, South Africa, August 2007)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10216466/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

